Dialogue: 2,0:00:00.45,0:00:05.92,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,本期视频由Squarespace倾情赞助，助您轻松打造精美绝伦的网站
Dialogue: 1,0:00:00.45,0:00:05.92,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,This video is sponsored by Squarespace, the easiest way to create a beautiful website.
Dialogue: 2,0:00:07.06,0:00:12.59,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,回想起电影的早期峥嵘岁月，脑海中浮现的很可能是黑白影像
Dialogue: 1,0:00:07.06,0:00:12.59,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,When you think of the early days of film, black and white images will likely come to mind,
Dialogue: 2,0:00:12.59,0:00:18.09,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,银幕上的世界，全然由单色的灰阶描绘而成
Dialogue: 1,0:00:12.59,0:00:18.09,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,with cinematic worlds exclusively portrayed in monochromatic shades of grey.
Dialogue: 2,0:00:18.42,0:00:22.86,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,然而，特艺彩色（Technicolor）的到来，宛如一道色彩的闪光
Dialogue: 1,0:00:18.42,0:00:22.86,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,But then, like a flash of colour itself, Technicolor arrived, 
Dialogue: 2,0:00:22.86,0:00:27.99,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,彻底革新了我们在大银幕上体验故事的方式
Dialogue: 1,0:00:22.86,0:00:27.99,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,revolutionising the very way we experience storytelling on the big screen.
Dialogue: 2,0:00:28.35,0:00:32.87,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,从《绿野仙踪》中郁郁葱葱，饱满的景色
Dialogue: 1,0:00:28.35,0:00:32.87,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,From the lush, saturated landscapes of the Wizard of Oz, 
Dialogue: 2,0:00:32.87,0:00:36.39,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,到《红菱艳》里精致绝伦的色调
Dialogue: 1,0:00:32.87,0:00:36.39,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,to the exquisite palettes in the red shoes,
Dialogue: 2,0:00:36.39,0:00:42.54,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,它不再仅仅是一种工具，更成为了电影魔力的象征
Dialogue: 1,0:00:36.39,0:00:42.54,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,it became more than just a tool, it became a symbol of cinematic magic.
Dialogue: 2,0:00:42.85,0:00:47.41,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,让我们一同探寻特艺彩色的技术演进与历史轨迹
Dialogue: 1,0:00:42.85,0:00:47.41,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Let's explore the technical evolution and history of Technicolor,
Dialogue: 2,0:00:47.41,0:00:51.63,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,看看这一开创性的工艺如何为画面注入生命
Dialogue: 1,0:00:47.41,0:00:51.63,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,and look at how this groundbreaking process brought Hughes to life, 
Dialogue: 2,0:00:51.63,0:00:54.59,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,并永远地改变了电影制作
Dialogue: 1,0:00:51.63,0:00:54.59,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,transforming filmmaking forever.
Dialogue: 2,0:00:58.25,0:01:02.73,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,在二十世纪初，电影制作尚处萌芽阶段
Dialogue: 1,0:00:58.25,0:01:02.73,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,At the start of the 1900s, when filmmaking was still in its infancy,
Dialogue: 2,0:01:02.73,0:01:06.43,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,一些技术先驱，如爱德华·特纳
Dialogue: 1,0:01:02.73,0:01:06.43,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,a few technical innovators, such as Edward Turner, 
Dialogue: 2,0:01:06.43,0:01:11.49,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,开始尝试制作35毫米的彩色胶片拷贝
Dialogue: 1,0:01:06.43,0:01:11.49,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,began toying with the idea of creating a 35mm colour print.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:11.92,0:01:15.89,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,然而，这些早期的实验可称得上凤毛麟角
Dialogue: 1,0:01:11.92,0:01:15.89,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,However, these early experiments were few and far between,
Dialogue: 2,0:01:15.89,0:01:21.90,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,直到1909年前后，首个主流的彩色电影摄影工艺
Dialogue: 1,0:01:15.89,0:01:21.90,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,until around 1909, where the first major colour cinematography process,
Dialogue: 2,0:01:21.90,0:01:25.55,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,一种名为Kinemacolor的技术，在英国应运而生
Dialogue: 1,0:01:21.90,0:01:25.55,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,called Kinemacolor, was invented in Britain.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:26.13,0:01:29.71,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,1915年其商业应用日渐式微后
Dialogue: 1,0:01:26.13,0:01:29.71,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,After commercial use faded in 1915, 
Dialogue: 2,0:01:29.71,0:01:32.45,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,特艺彩色便接踵而至
Dialogue: 1,0:01:29.71,0:01:32.45,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,it was followed by Technicolor.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:32.86,0:01:36.12,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,但这项技术究竟是如何运作的呢？
Dialogue: 1,0:01:32.86,0:01:36.12,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,But how exactly did this technology work?
Dialogue: 2,0:01:36.89,0:01:41.35,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,特艺彩色试图以一种近乎魔幻的方式创造彩色影像
Dialogue: 1,0:01:36.89,0:01:41.35,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Technicolor sought to almost magically create a colour image,
Dialogue: 2,0:01:41.35,0:01:45.65,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,同时利用的却是当时已有的黑白胶片
Dialogue: 1,0:01:41.35,0:01:45.65,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,while using the black and white film which was available at the time.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:46.36,0:01:52.24,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,其最初的迭代，被称为一号工艺（Process 1），采用的是双色系统
Dialogue: 1,0:01:46.36,0:01:52.24,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,The first iteration, which was called Process 1, used a two colour system.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:52.95,0:01:56.24,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,基本上就是将每一帧画面记录两次
Dialogue: 1,0:01:52.95,0:01:56.24,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Basically, it recorded each frame twice,
Dialogue: 2,0:01:56.24,0:02:00.17,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,记录在同一卷35毫米黑白胶片上
Dialogue: 1,0:01:56.24,0:02:00.17,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,on one roll of 35mm black and white film,
Dialogue: 2,0:02:00.17,0:02:03.96,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,分别透过一片绿色滤镜和一片红色滤镜
Dialogue: 1,0:02:00.17,0:02:03.96,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,behind a green filter, and a red filter.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:04.96,0:02:08.67,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,该过程由一台特制的特艺彩色摄影机完成
Dialogue: 1,0:02:04.96,0:02:08.67,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,This was done by a specialist Technicolor camera,
Dialogue: 2,0:02:08.67,0:02:13.10,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,最初由沃尔瑟姆机械公司制造
Dialogue: 1,0:02:08.67,0:02:13.10,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,which was initially manufactured by the Waltham Machine Company,
Dialogue: 2,0:02:13.10,0:02:18.88,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,后来被主导早期摄影机制造业的米切尔公司接管
Dialogue: 1,0:02:13.10,0:02:18.88,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,before it was taken over by Mitchell, who dominated early camera manufacturing.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:19.50,0:02:22.99,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,为了能同时记录这两个影像
Dialogue: 1,0:02:19.50,0:02:22.99,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,To record these two moving images at the same time,
Dialogue: 2,0:02:22.99,0:02:26.55,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这台特艺彩色摄影机使用了一个分光镜
Dialogue: 1,0:02:22.99,0:02:26.55,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,this Technicolor camera used a beam splitter,
Dialogue: 2,0:02:26.55,0:02:31.92,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,光线进入镜头后，被分流至两个区域
Dialogue: 1,0:02:26.55,0:02:31.92,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,where light entered the lens, and was then diverted into two areas,
Dialogue: 2,0:02:32.37,0:02:35.36,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,借助光学元件，通过不同的片门
Dialogue: 1,0:02:32.37,0:02:35.36,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,through different gates, using optics.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:35.85,0:02:39.84,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这使得两个影像能被分别曝光
Dialogue: 1,0:02:35.85,0:02:39.84,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,This allowed two images to be individually exposed to light,
Dialogue: 2,0:02:39.84,0:02:44.25,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,并并列记录在同一条胶片上
Dialogue: 1,0:02:39.84,0:02:44.25,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,and recorded next to each other on the same strip of film.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:45.13,0:02:50.12,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,随后，胶片拷贝可通过一台带双镜头的特制放映机播放
Dialogue: 1,0:02:45.13,0:02:50.12,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Later, a film print could be played back by a special projector with two lenses.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:50.60,0:02:54.50,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,其中一个镜头的光圈会产生红色调的影像
Dialogue: 1,0:02:50.60,0:02:54.50,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,One with an aperture which created a red tinted image,
Dialogue: 2,0:02:54.50,0:02:57.03,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,另一个则带着绿色的光圈
Dialogue: 1,0:02:54.50,0:02:57.03,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,and the other with a green aperture.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:57.86,0:03:02.45,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,当这两个不同色彩的影像被精确定位
Dialogue: 1,0:02:57.86,0:03:02.45,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,When these two different coloured images were positioned correctly,
Dialogue: 2,0:03:02.45,0:03:05.78,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,使它们在放映幕布上相互重叠
Dialogue: 1,0:03:02.45,0:03:05.78,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,so that they overlapped each other on the projection screen,
Dialogue: 2,0:03:05.78,0:03:10.03,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,便能产生活动影像的色彩雏形
Dialogue: 1,0:03:05.78,0:03:10.03,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,they produced very rudimentary moving colour footage.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:10.59,0:03:13.74,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,因为仅融合了两种颜色
Dialogue: 1,0:03:10.59,0:03:13.74,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Because just two colours were combined,
Dialogue: 2,0:03:13.74,0:03:18.01,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,早期的特艺彩色只能呈现极为有限的色彩范围
Dialogue: 1,0:03:13.74,0:03:18.01,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,early Technicolor could only produce a very limited range of colours.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:18.50,0:03:20.25,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,他们选择了红色与绿色
Dialogue: 1,0:03:18.50,0:03:20.25,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,They chose red and green,
Dialogue: 2,0:03:20.25,0:03:25.52,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,因为他们想优先还原肤色与绿色的植物
Dialogue: 1,0:03:20.25,0:03:25.52,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,because they wanted to prioritise skin tone colours, and greener foliage. 
Dialogue: 2,0:03:25.90,0:03:29.67,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,然而，这牺牲了捕捉其他色调的能力
Dialogue: 1,0:03:25.90,0:03:29.67,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,However, at the expense of not capturing other hues,
Dialogue: 2,0:03:29.67,0:03:32.13,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,例如蓝色或紫色
Dialogue: 1,0:03:29.67,0:03:32.13,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,like blues or purples.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:33.28,0:03:37.68,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,将这两个投射影像相结合的方式，被称为“加色法”
Dialogue: 1,0:03:33.28,0:03:37.68,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Combining these two projected images was called the additive colour process.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:38.42,0:03:41.68,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,然而，它伴随着许多技术难题
Dialogue: 1,0:03:38.42,0:03:41.68,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,However, it came with many technical glitches,
Dialogue: 2,0:03:41.68,0:03:46.74,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,比如放映技师需要频繁地重新校准
Dialogue: 1,0:03:41.68,0:03:46.74,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,such as the projector technician needing to very frequently recalibrate,
Dialogue: 2,0:03:46.74,0:03:50.95,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,并调整放映机镜头的对齐位置
Dialogue: 1,0:03:46.74,0:03:50.95,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,and reposition the alignment of the projector lenses.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:51.42,0:03:54.76,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这第一套工艺从未真正流行起来
Dialogue: 1,0:03:51.42,0:03:54.76,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,This first process never really took off.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:55.01,0:04:01.21,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,不过它促使特艺彩色重返绘图板，着手开发二号工艺
Dialogue: 1,0:03:55.01,0:04:01.21,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,However, it did send Technicolor back to the drawing board to develop process number 2.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:04.32,0:04:07.78,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,特艺彩色二号工艺没有改变双色摄影系统
Dialogue: 1,0:04:04.32,0:04:07.78,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Rather than changing the two colour camera system,
Dialogue: 2,0:04:07.78,0:04:13.51,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,而是决定改进胶片的放映方式
Dialogue: 1,0:04:07.78,0:04:13.51,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Technicolor process 2 decided to alter how the film projection happened.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:13.92,0:04:17.50,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,相较于第一套工艺的加色法
Dialogue: 1,0:04:13.92,0:04:17.50,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Instead of the first process's additive colour,
Dialogue: 2,0:04:17.50,0:04:20.89,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这项新工艺采用了减色法
Dialogue: 1,0:04:17.50,0:04:20.89,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,this new process used subtractive colour.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:21.15,0:04:26.17,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这意味着它不再投射两个独立的红、绿影像
Dialogue: 1,0:04:21.15,0:04:26.17,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,What this meant was that rather than projecting two separate red and green images,
Dialogue: 2,0:04:26.69,0:04:32.45,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,减色法将它们合成为一个35毫米的彩色拷贝
Dialogue: 1,0:04:26.69,0:04:32.45,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,subtractive colour combined them into one 35mm colour print,
Dialogue: 2,0:04:32.45,0:04:35.21,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,可以直接通过普通放映机播放
Dialogue: 1,0:04:32.45,0:04:35.21,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,which could be run through an ordinary projector.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:36.20,0:04:41.57,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,经由特艺彩色摄影机，透过红、绿滤镜拍摄的35毫米黑白胶片
Dialogue: 1,0:04:36.20,0:04:41.57,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Once the 35mm black and white film rolls that were shot with a red and a green filter
Dialogue: 2,0:04:41.57,0:04:46.10,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,一旦完成冲洗与印片
Dialogue: 1,0:04:41.57,0:04:46.10,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,by the Technicolor camera were developed and printed,
Dialogue: 2,0:04:46.10,0:04:48.22,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,它们就会被黏合在一起
Dialogue: 1,0:04:46.10,0:04:48.22,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,they were stuck together,
Dialogue: 2,0:04:48.22,0:04:52.06,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,然后在实验室中使用不同的染料进行染色
Dialogue: 1,0:04:48.22,0:04:52.06,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,then colour toned in a lab using different dyes.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:52.38,0:04:55.71,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,来自绿色通道的黑白胶片
Dialogue: 1,0:04:52.38,0:04:55.71,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,The black and white film from the green side 
Dialogue: 2,0:04:55.71,0:05:00.89,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,会被赋予一种互补的，或者说相反的橘红色调
Dialogue: 1,0:04:55.71,0:05:00.89,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,was given a complementary or opposite red-orange tint,
Dialogue: 2,0:05:01.41,0:05:06.79,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,而来自红色通道的胶片，则会被染上青绿色调
Dialogue: 1,0:05:01.41,0:05:06.79,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,while the film from the red side was given a green cyan tint.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:07.14,0:05:10.82,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,当两者结合，便能生成一份基本的彩色拷贝
Dialogue: 1,0:05:07.14,0:05:10.82,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,When combined, these produced a basic colour print,
Dialogue: 2,0:05:10.82,0:05:13.75,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,可在电影院进行放映
Dialogue: 1,0:05:10.82,0:05:13.75,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,which could be projected in cinemas.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:14.34,0:05:18.24,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,尽管这极大地简化了放映流程
Dialogue: 1,0:05:14.34,0:05:18.24,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Although this vastly simplified the projection process
Dialogue: 2,0:05:18.24,0:05:22.37,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,并提升了影院成片的质量控制
Dialogue: 1,0:05:18.24,0:05:22.37,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,and increased the quality control of the product in cinemas,
Dialogue: 2,0:05:22.37,0:05:25.54,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,它依然存在一些缺陷
Dialogue: 1,0:05:22.37,0:05:25.54,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,it still came with a number of downsides.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:25.97,0:05:32.09,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,其中一些问题在1928年更新的特艺彩色三号工艺中得到了解决
Dialogue: 1,0:05:25.97,0:05:32.09,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Some of these issues were addressed in the updated 1928 Technicolor Process 3,
Dialogue: 2,0:05:32.09,0:05:35.14,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,它使得胶片拷贝更坚韧，更耐久
Dialogue: 1,0:05:32.09,0:05:35.14,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,which made the print more hardy, durable,
Dialogue: 2,0:05:35.14,0:05:41.45,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,不易刮伤，并且能在影院放映更长时间而不受损
Dialogue: 1,0:05:35.14,0:05:41.45,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,less prone to scratching and able to play in cinemas for longer without getting damaged.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:42.34,0:05:45.09,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,尽管技术已然精进
Dialogue: 1,0:05:42.34,0:05:45.09,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Despite the improvement in the technology,
Dialogue: 2,0:05:45.09,0:05:48.09,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,特艺彩色公司仍未完全满足
Dialogue: 1,0:05:45.09,0:05:48.09,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Technicolor was still not entirely happy,
Dialogue: 2,0:05:48.09,0:05:51.54,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,他们寻求发明一种全新的最终工艺
Dialogue: 1,0:05:48.09,0:05:51.54,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,and sought to invent a new final process,
Dialogue: 2,0:05:51.54,0:05:54.41,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,能够向观众呈现一个完整
Dialogue: 1,0:05:51.54,0:05:54.41,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,which would be able to present a full, 
Dialogue: 2,0:05:54.41,0:05:58.29,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,饱满，且绚丽的色彩光谱
Dialogue: 1,0:05:54.41,0:05:58.29,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,saturated spectrum of vivid colour to audiences.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:59.67,0:06:03.53,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,在我们转向第四个，也是最终的特艺彩色工艺之前
Dialogue: 1,0:05:59.67,0:06:03.53,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Before we move on to the fourth and final Technicolor Process,
Dialogue: 2,0:06:03.53,0:06:06.49,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我需要感谢今天的赞助商，Squarespace
Dialogue: 1,0:06:03.53,0:06:06.49,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,I need to thank today's sponsor, Squarespace.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.53,0:06:06.49,Yahei-1920x1080,atg3,0,0,0,,广告空降7:04
Dialogue: 2,0:07:04.05,0:07:11.14,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,双色工艺除了技术上的不足，其主要的缺憾在于美学层面
Dialogue: 1,0:07:04.05,0:07:11.14,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Apart from the technical downsides of the two colour process, the main negative was an aesthetic one.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:11.52,0:07:19.28,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,仅用两种颜色来记录和染色胶片，严重限制了它能再现的色彩范围
Dialogue: 1,0:07:11.52,0:07:19.28,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Recording and toning film with only two colours severely limited the spectrum of colours it could reproduce.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:20.02,0:07:26.68,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,为了克服这一点，他们决定将可记录的颜色从两种提升至三种
Dialogue: 1,0:07:20.02,0:07:26.68,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,To overcome this, they decided to bump up the colours they could record from 2 to 3.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:27.11,0:07:32.65,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这需要与米切尔公司合作，制造一台全新的摄影机
Dialogue: 1,0:07:27.11,0:07:32.65,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,This required manufacturing a whole new camera in collaboration with Mitchell.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:33.02,0:07:35.06,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,当光线穿过镜头
Dialogue: 1,0:07:33.02,0:07:35.06,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Once the light passed through the lens,
Dialogue: 2,0:07:35.06,0:07:40.22,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,它再次被分光镜在光学上分为两股不同的光束
Dialogue: 1,0:07:35.06,0:07:40.22,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,it was again optically divided into two different streams by the beam splitter.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:40.66,0:07:44.42,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,然而，这一次，不再是记录在一卷胶片上
Dialogue: 1,0:07:40.66,0:07:44.42,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,However, this time, instead of recording to one roll of film,
Dialogue: 2,0:07:44.75,0:07:52.41,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,每一帧画面被同时记录在三卷不同的35毫米黑白胶片上
Dialogue: 1,0:07:44.75,0:07:52.41,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,each frame was recorded onto three different rolls of 35mm black and white film simultaneously.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:53.65,0:08:01.73,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,一股光束被分离，穿过滤镜，使一卷胶片只对绿光曝光
Dialogue: 1,0:07:53.65,0:08:01.73,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,One stream of light was split, passed through a filter and exposed one film roll to only green light.
Dialogue: 2,0:08:02.31,0:08:06.97,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,另一股分离的光束首先被记录在一张正色片上
Dialogue: 1,0:08:02.31,0:08:06.97,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,The other split beam was first recorded onto an orthochromatic film,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.31,0:08:09.49,Yahei-1920x1080,atg3,0,0,0,,正色片是一种对波长580nm以下可见光感光的感光材料，其乳剂含有银盐和增感染料组成的化学涂层\n感色范围覆盖380-580nm波段的蓝紫光至黄绿光
Dialogue: 2,0:08:06.97,0:08:09.49,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,它只吸收蓝光
Dialogue: 1,0:08:06.97,0:08:09.49,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,which absorbed only blue light,
Dialogue: 2,0:08:09.85,0:08:13.53,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,然后再传递到第三张全色片上
Dialogue: 1,0:08:09.85,0:08:13.53,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,before then passing to a third panchromatic film,
Dialogue: 2,0:08:13.80,0:08:15.86,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,它只捕捉红光
Dialogue: 1,0:08:13.80,0:08:15.86,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,which captured only red light.
Dialogue: 2,0:08:17.10,0:08:21.48,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这三卷黑白负片随后被送往实验室
Dialogue: 1,0:08:17.10,0:08:21.48,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,These three rolls of black and white negative film were later sent to a lab
Dialogue: 2,0:08:21.48,0:08:24.67,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,在那里它们被冲洗成黑白正片
Dialogue: 1,0:08:21.48,0:08:24.67,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,where they were developed into a black and white positive,
Dialogue: 2,0:08:24.67,0:08:28.55,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,然后，如同早前的减色法工艺
Dialogue: 1,0:08:24.67,0:08:28.55,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,and then, like in the earlier subtractive colour process,
Dialogue: 2,0:08:28.55,0:08:34.45,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,它们被染上位于色谱另一端的染料
Dialogue: 1,0:08:28.55,0:08:34.45,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,they were toned with a dye that was on the opposite end of the colour spectrum.
Dialogue: 2,0:08:35.23,0:08:41.11,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,于是，对红光曝光的黑白胶片被染上青色
Dialogue: 1,0:08:35.23,0:08:41.11,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,So, the black and white film exposed to red light was given a cyan dye,
Dialogue: 2,0:08:41.47,0:08:45.64,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,用蓝光记录的影像被染上黄色
Dialogue: 1,0:08:41.47,0:08:45.64,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,the image recorded with blue light given a yellow dye,
Dialogue: 2,0:08:45.87,0:08:49.88,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,而绿光影像则被染成品红色
Dialogue: 1,0:08:45.87,0:08:49.88,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,and the green light image toned a magenta colour.
Dialogue: 2,0:08:50.96,0:08:56.50,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,当这些青色，黄色和品红色的影像合而为一
Dialogue: 1,0:08:50.96,0:08:56.50,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,When these cyan, yellow and magenta toned images were combined into one,
Dialogue: 2,0:08:56.50,0:09:00.72,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,它们便能生成更为精确的色彩再现
Dialogue: 1,0:08:56.50,0:09:00.72,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,they produced a much more accurate reproduction of colour,
Dialogue: 2,0:09:00.72,0:09:02.90,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,更接近人眼所见的真实世界
Dialogue: 1,0:09:00.72,0:09:02.90,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,closer to what the human eye sees.
Dialogue: 2,0:09:03.51,0:09:07.40,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,能够捕捉到以往无法实现的色调
Dialogue: 1,0:09:03.51,0:09:07.40,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Being able to capture tones which before weren't possible,
Dialogue: 2,0:09:07.40,0:09:11.10,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,比如蓝色以及介于其间的许多其他色彩
Dialogue: 1,0:09:07.40,0:09:11.10,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,such as blues and many other colours in between.
Dialogue: 2,0:09:11.51,0:09:14.60,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这项三色工艺首次引人注目的应用
Dialogue: 1,0:09:11.51,0:09:14.60,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,The first notable use of this three colour process,
Dialogue: 2,0:09:14.60,0:09:17.82,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,淋漓尽致地展现其宽广的色彩捕捉能力
Dialogue: 1,0:09:14.60,0:09:17.82,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,which showed off its broad range of colour capture,
Dialogue: 2,0:09:17.82,0:09:22.33,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,是在迪士尼的动画短片《花与树》中
Dialogue: 1,0:09:17.82,0:09:22.33,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,was on the Disney animated short, Flowers and Trees.
Dialogue: 2,0:09:22.85,0:09:26.88,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这种染料的组合创造出一种独特的特艺彩色质感
Dialogue: 1,0:09:22.85,0:09:26.88,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,This combination of dyes created a unique technic colour look,
Dialogue: 2,0:09:26.88,0:09:32.00,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,成为了从30年代初到50年代彩色电影的代表
Dialogue: 1,0:09:26.88,0:09:32.00,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,that came to represent colour cinema from the early 30s to the 50s.
Dialogue: 2,0:09:32.34,0:09:35.68,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,它拥有鲜明，浓郁，饱和的色彩
Dialogue: 1,0:09:32.34,0:09:35.68,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,It had vivid, rich, saturated colours,
Dialogue: 2,0:09:36.00,0:09:40.87,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,其中红色，橙色和黄色尤为醒目
Dialogue: 1,0:09:36.00,0:09:40.87,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,with reds, oranges and yellows being particularly punchy,
Dialogue: 2,0:09:40.87,0:09:47.85,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,而在明亮光线下，较浅的肤色则呈现出一种奶油般的古铜色柔和暖调
Dialogue: 1,0:09:40.87,0:09:47.85,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,and brightly lit, paler skin tones having a creamy bronze pastel warmth.
Dialogue: 2,0:09:48.36,0:09:51.18,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这种增强的饱和度与对比度
Dialogue: 1,0:09:48.36,0:09:51.18,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,This boosted saturation and contrast,
Dialogue: 2,0:09:51.18,0:09:54.72,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,意味着较暗的阴影常常被压缩成纯黑
Dialogue: 1,0:09:51.18,0:09:54.72,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,meant that darker shadows were often crushed to pure black,
Dialogue: 2,0:09:54.72,0:09:56.42,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,并且缺乏细节
Dialogue: 1,0:09:54.72,0:09:56.42,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,and lacked detail.
Dialogue: 2,0:09:56.82,0:09:59.60,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,西装变成了一团没有纹理的深色块
Dialogue: 1,0:09:56.82,0:09:59.60,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Suits became dark blobs without texture.
Dialogue: 2,0:10:00.67,0:10:03.32,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这种色彩明亮而富有冲击力的特质
Dialogue: 1,0:10:00.67,0:10:03.32,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,The bright punchy quality of this colour,
Dialogue: 2,0:10:03.32,0:10:08.18,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,使其在好莱坞常被用于较为轻松愉快的类型片
Dialogue: 1,0:10:03.32,0:10:08.18,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,meant it was often used in Hollywood for lighter entertaining genres,
Dialogue: 2,0:10:08.44,0:10:13.57,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,例如歌舞片，动画片，冒险片或喜剧片
Dialogue: 1,0:10:08.44,0:10:13.57,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,such as musicals, animation, adventure or comedies.
Dialogue: 2,0:10:13.82,0:10:19.13,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,而黑白影像则常常为色调更暗，更具戏剧性的电影保留
Dialogue: 1,0:10:13.82,0:10:19.13,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,While black and white was often preserved for darker, more dramatic films,
Dialogue: 2,0:10:19.13,0:10:21.28,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,比如黑色电影类型
Dialogue: 1,0:10:19.13,0:10:21.28,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,such as in the noir genre.
Dialogue: 2,0:10:21.63,0:10:25.02,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,然而，也有某些电影制作人选择了特艺彩色
Dialogue: 1,0:10:21.63,0:10:25.02,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,However, certain filmmakers did opt for technicolour,
Dialogue: 2,0:10:25.02,0:10:29.38,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,为一些戏剧性的史诗巨制创造视觉奇观
Dialogue: 1,0:10:25.02,0:10:29.38,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,to create a visual spectacle for some dramatic epics.
Dialogue: 2,0:10:31.00,0:10:35.17,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,尽管这项三色工艺极大地改善了画面效果
Dialogue: 1,0:10:31.00,0:10:35.17,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Even though this three colour process vastly improved both the look,
Dialogue: 2,0:10:35.17,0:10:39.17,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,以及早期工艺在放映上的局限
Dialogue: 1,0:10:35.17,0:10:39.17,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,and the projection limitations of the earlier processes,
Dialogue: 2,0:10:39.17,0:10:41.73,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,它也并非没有瑕疵
Dialogue: 1,0:10:39.17,0:10:41.73,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,it wasn't without some flaws.
Dialogue: 2,0:10:42.75,0:10:48.21,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,首先，使用这种三色特艺彩色工艺进行拍摄是昂贵的
Dialogue: 1,0:10:42.75,0:10:48.21,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Firstly, shooting in this three colour technicolour process was expensive.
Dialogue: 2,0:10:48.64,0:10:50.62,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,由于需要三卷胶片
Dialogue: 1,0:10:48.64,0:10:50.62,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,With their three film rolls,
Dialogue: 2,0:10:50.62,0:10:57.79,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,它们使用的35毫米胶片量至少是黑白电影拍摄的三倍
Dialogue: 1,0:10:50.62,0:10:57.79,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,they used at least triple the amount of 35mm film, compared to movies shot in black and white. 
Dialogue: 2,0:10:58.49,0:11:03.75,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,此外，这项工艺需要实验室进行更复杂的处理工作
Dialogue: 1,0:10:58.49,0:11:03.75,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Additionally, this process required more complex processing work in the lab,
Dialogue: 2,0:11:03.75,0:11:07.74,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,来冲洗胶片并制作彩色放映拷贝
Dialogue: 1,0:11:03.75,0:11:07.74,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,to develop the film and to make the colour projection print.
Dialogue: 2,0:11:08.32,0:11:13.05,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,电影制片厂也无法购买自己的三色米切尔摄影机
Dialogue: 1,0:11:08.32,0:11:13.05,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Film studios also couldn't buy their own three colour Mitchell cameras,
Dialogue: 2,0:11:13.05,0:11:16.50,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,只得从特艺彩色公司租用
Dialogue: 1,0:11:13.05,0:11:16.50,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,but were instead forced to rent them from technicolour,
Dialogue: 2,0:11:16.50,0:11:21.12,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,同时还要雇用他们的一位摄影技师和色彩总监
Dialogue: 1,0:11:16.50,0:11:21.12,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,along with one of their camera technicians and colour supervisors,
Dialogue: 2,0:11:21.12,0:11:25.40,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,他们要确保镜头前的服装和布景色彩
Dialogue: 1,0:11:21.12,0:11:25.40,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,who made sure that the hues of the costumes and sets in front of the camera,
Dialogue: 2,0:11:25.40,0:11:28.08,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,不会超出摄影机的能力极限
Dialogue: 1,0:11:25.40,0:11:28.08,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,didn't push the camera's limitations.
Dialogue: 2,0:11:28.74,0:11:33.21,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,因此，特艺彩色通常只为高预算的电影保留
Dialogue: 1,0:11:28.74,0:11:33.21,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Technicolour was therefore often reserved for higher budget films.
Dialogue: 2,0:11:33.62,0:11:38.08,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,或者偶尔只用于几个特定的重要场景
Dialogue: 1,0:11:33.62,0:11:38.08,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Or occasionally only used for a few select set pieces,
Dialogue: 2,0:11:38.08,0:11:41.21,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,而电影的其余部分则用黑白拍摄
Dialogue: 1,0:11:38.08,0:11:41.21,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,with the rest of the movie shot in black and white.
Dialogue: 2,0:11:41.83,0:11:46.99,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,除了成本，电影摄影师和剧组人员也面临挑战
Dialogue: 1,0:11:41.83,0:11:46.99,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Apart from the cast, cinematographers and crews were also challenged.
Dialogue: 2,0:11:47.33,0:11:50.60,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,由于有一套分离光束的棱镜系统
Dialogue: 1,0:11:47.33,0:11:50.60,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Due to the prism system that split the light beam,
Dialogue: 2,0:11:50.60,0:11:54.95,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,以及当时黑白胶片感光速度较低
Dialogue: 1,0:11:50.60,0:11:54.95,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,along with the low speeds of the black and white film stock of the time,
Dialogue: 2,0:11:54.95,0:11:58.02,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,他们不得不将胶片的感光度定得极低
Dialogue: 1,0:11:54.95,0:11:58.02,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,they had to rate the film incredibly low,
Dialogue: 2,0:11:58.02,0:12:00.99,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,大约仅为5 ASA
Dialogue: 1,0:11:58.02,0:12:00.99,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,at around a mere 5 ASA.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.02,0:12:00.99,Yahei-1920x1080,atg3,0,0,0,,ASA感光度是由美国标准协会（American Standards Association，ASA）制定的感光材料标准
Dialogue: 2,0:12:01.30,0:12:04.38,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这需要巨量的光线
Dialogue: 1,0:12:01.30,0:12:04.38,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,This required an enormous amount of light,
Dialogue: 2,0:12:04.38,0:12:07.39,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,尤其是在为大型布景打光时
Dialogue: 1,0:12:04.38,0:12:07.39,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,especially when lighting large sets.
Dialogue: 2,0:12:07.85,0:12:11.17,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这种光通常来自碳弧灯
Dialogue: 1,0:12:07.85,0:12:11.17,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,This light usually came from carbon arc sources,
Dialogue: 2,0:12:11.17,0:12:14.57,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,其运行时温度极高，甚至会冒烟
Dialogue: 1,0:12:11.17,0:12:14.57,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,which ran so hot that they would smoke,
Dialogue: 2,0:12:14.82,0:12:18.78,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,将片场的温度提升到酷热的程度
Dialogue: 1,0:12:14.82,0:12:18.78,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,raising the temperature's onsets to extreme heights.
Dialogue: 2,0:12:19.29,0:12:22.18,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,另一个实际的缺点是声音
Dialogue: 1,0:12:19.29,0:12:22.18,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Another practical downside was sound.
Dialogue: 2,0:12:22.58,0:12:25.52,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,当35毫米胶片在摄影机中运转时
Dialogue: 1,0:12:22.58,0:12:25.52,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,When 35mm film runs through a camera,
Dialogue: 2,0:12:25.52,0:12:27.83,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,会发出嗡嗡的声响
Dialogue: 1,0:12:25.52,0:12:27.83,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,it makes a whirring sound.
Dialogue: 2,0:12:28.51,0:12:32.36,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,由于三倍的胶片量通过摄影机
Dialogue: 1,0:12:28.51,0:12:32.36,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Having three times the amount of film passed through the camera,
Dialogue: 2,0:12:32.36,0:12:35.11,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,搞得这些摄影机非常嘈杂
Dialogue: 1,0:12:32.36,0:12:35.11,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,made these cameras very noisy.
Dialogue: 2,0:12:35.11,0:12:38.06,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,以至于无法用它们录制同期声
Dialogue: 1,0:12:35.11,0:12:38.06,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,So much so that you couldn't record sync sound with them,
Dialogue: 2,0:12:38.14,0:12:40.87,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,除非使用所谓的隔音罩
Dialogue: 1,0:12:38.14,0:12:40.87,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,without using what was called a blimp,
Dialogue: 2,0:12:40.87,0:12:43.56,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,一种能减弱摄影机噪音的罩子
Dialogue: 1,0:12:40.87,0:12:43.56,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,a cover that dampens the camera noise.
Dialogue: 2,0:12:44.09,0:12:48.98,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,用于这些特艺彩色米切尔摄影机的隔音罩大得离谱
Dialogue: 1,0:12:44.09,0:12:48.98,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,The blimps for these Technicolor Mitchell cameras were outrageously big,
Dialogue: 2,0:12:48.98,0:12:52.94,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,使得移动这个沉重的庞然大物
Dialogue: 1,0:12:48.98,0:12:52.94,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,and made moving this heavy hunk of machinery around
Dialogue: 2,0:12:52.94,0:12:56.70,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,比使用标准的米切尔摄影机要困难得多
Dialogue: 1,0:12:52.94,0:12:56.70,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,much more difficult than with a standard Mitchell camera.
Dialogue: 2,0:12:58.60,0:13:04.67,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,三色特艺彩色从30年代初到50年代中期，有过一段辉煌的历程
Dialogue: 1,0:12:58.60,0:13:04.67,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Three color Technicolor had a great run from the early 30s to the mid 50s,
Dialogue: 2,0:13:04.67,0:13:07.81,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,拍摄了许多经典的好莱坞电影
Dialogue: 1,0:13:04.67,0:13:07.81,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,shooting many iconic Hollywood films.
Dialogue: 2,0:13:08.38,0:13:12.60,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,然而，特艺彩色的落寞是柯达公司造成的
Dialogue: 1,0:13:08.38,0:13:12.60,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,However, the death of Technicolor was inflicted by Kodak
Dialogue: 2,0:13:12.60,0:13:14.19,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,50年代早期
Dialogue: 1,0:13:12.60,0:13:14.19,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,in the early 50s,
Dialogue: 2,0:13:14.19,0:13:19.06,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,随着35毫米电影彩色负片的问世
Dialogue: 1,0:13:14.19,0:13:19.06,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,with the invention of 35mm motion picture color negative film.
Dialogue: 2,0:13:19.59,0:13:24.74,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这种伊士曼彩色负片，或ECN胶片工艺
Dialogue: 1,0:13:19.59,0:13:24.74,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,This Eastman color negative, or ECN film process,
Dialogue: 2,0:13:24.74,0:13:28.24,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,意味着不再需要庞大的摄影机
Dialogue: 1,0:13:24.74,0:13:28.24,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,meant that instead of needing an enormous camera,
Dialogue: 2,0:13:28.24,0:13:30.08,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,三卷黑白胶片
Dialogue: 1,0:13:28.24,0:13:30.08,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,three rolls of black and white film,
Dialogue: 2,0:13:30.12,0:13:33.38,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,和复杂的实验室染色过程
Dialogue: 1,0:13:30.12,0:13:33.38,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,and a complex laboratory dyeing process,
Dialogue: 2,0:13:33.82,0:13:37.70,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,你所需要的只是一台随便什么型号的35毫米电影摄影机
Dialogue: 1,0:13:33.82,0:13:37.70,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,all you needed was any 35mm motion picture camera,
Dialogue: 2,0:13:37.70,0:13:40.17,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,和一卷胶片
Dialogue: 1,0:13:37.70,0:13:40.17,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,and a single roll of film.
Dialogue: 2,0:13:40.17,0:13:44.05,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,经过冲洗，就能立刻得到彩色影像
Dialogue: 1,0:13:40.17,0:13:44.05,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,which, when processed, would give an immediate color image.
Dialogue: 2,0:13:44.45,0:13:50.52,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,虽然ECN的画面饱和度较低，色调比特艺彩色更柔和
Dialogue: 1,0:13:44.45,0:13:50.52,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Although the look of ECN was less saturated and more muted than Technicolor,
Dialogue: 2,0:13:50.52,0:13:58.52,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,但彩色负片的便捷性，人体工程学和经济性最终胜出
Dialogue: 1,0:13:50.52,0:13:58.52,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,the ease, ergonomics, and economics of color negative film ultimately won out,
Dialogue: 2,0:13:58.52,0:14:06.10,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,留下了特艺彩色以及那批饱满，浓郁，充满愉悦的美丽影片，成为永恒的经典
Dialogue: 1,0:13:58.52,0:14:06.10,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,leaving behind Technicolor and its beautiful collection of saturated, rich, joyful films.
Dialogue: 2,0:14:08.46,0:14:11.27,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,感谢大家对本频道的支持
Dialogue: 1,0:14:08.46,0:14:11.27,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Thanks to everyone for supporting the channel,
Dialogue: 2,0:14:11.27,0:14:15.03,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,特别是Patreon上的朋友们，是你们让频道得以持续
Dialogue: 1,0:14:11.27,0:14:15.03,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,especially those on Patreon who keep the channel going.
Dialogue: 2,0:14:15.32,0:14:19.23,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,那么，下次再见，感谢收看，再会
Dialogue: 1,0:14:15.32,0:14:19.23,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Otherwise, until next time, thanks for watching and goodbye.